From: Zaid Ahmad <109442753+zaidahmad16@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 26 Apr 2026
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: bypass HT basic MCS check for non-STRICT hardware

Some APs (e.g. Comcast/Xfinity XB10, Rogers XB10) advertise a bogus HT
Operation basic MCS set that requires optional unequal-modulation MCS
indices (33-76) that most 2x2 cards cannot satisfy. This causes
ieee80211_verify_sta_ht_mcs_support() to return false, which causes
mac80211 to fall back to legacy 54 Mbps instead of connecting at proper
HT/VHT/HE speeds.

The VHT path already skips this check for non-STRICT hardware for the
same reason. Apply the same bypass here so that only explicitly strict
drivers enforce the basic MCS set. Non-strict hardware (including
Intel AX200/iwlmvm) will now ignore the bogus advertised MCS set and
negotiate the actual rate based on real capabilities.

Tested on Ubuntu 6.17 kernel with Intel AX200 against a Rogers XB10
gateway: link speed went from 54 Mbps (legacy) to 864 Mbps (HE 80 MHz
2x2) after applying this patch.

Signed-off-by: Zaid Ahmad <109442753+zaidahmad16@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 net/mac80211/mlme.c | 16 ++++++++--------
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/mlme.c b/net/mac80211/mlme.c
index abda6f91a..e6ae785fb 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/mlme.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/mlme.c
@@ -363,15 +363,15 @@ ieee80211_verify_sta_ht_mcs_support(struct ieee80211_sub_if_data *sdata,
 	ieee80211_apply_htcap_overrides(sdata, &sta_ht_cap);

 	/*
-	 * P802.11REVme/D7.0 - 6.5.4.2.4
-	 * ...
-	 * If the MLME of an HT STA receives an MLME-JOIN.request primitive
-	 * with the SelectedBSS parameter containing a Basic HT-MCS Set field
-	 * in the HT Operation parameter that contains any unsupported MCSs,
-	 * the MLME response in the resulting MLME-JOIN.confirm primitive shall
-	 * contain a ResultCode parameter that is not set to the value SUCCESS.
-	 * ...
+	 * Some APs (e.g. Comcast/Xfinity XB10) advertise a bogus HT Operation
+	 * basic MCS set that requires optional unequal-modulation MCS indices
+	 * (33-76) that most 2x2 cards cannot satisfy, causing a spurious HT
+	 * downgrade to legacy 54 Mbps.  The VHT path already skips this check
+	 * for non-STRICT hardware for the same reason; apply the same bypass
+	 * here so that only explicitly strict drivers enforce the basic MCS set.
 	 */
+	if (!ieee80211_hw_check(&sdata->local->hw, STRICT))
+		return true;

 	/* Simply check that all basic rates are in the STA RX mask */
 	for (i = 0; i < IEEE80211_HT_MCS_MASK_LEN; i++) {
--
